## When to use this component

Use this component when you need to present content, such as guidance or search results, across multiple pages.

You might do this when:
- showing all the content on a single page makes the page take too long to load
- users may benefit from bookmarking or linking to specific pages of the content
- most users will only need the content on the first pages

## When not to use this component

Only break up content into pages if it improves the performance or usability of your service.

Avoid using the 'infinite scroll' technique to automatically load content when the user approaches the bottom of the page. This causes problems for keyboard users.

## How it works

Add the pagination component after the content on each page that you have broken up.

[View an example of the component in a standard GOV.UK page template](in-page/index.html).

For pages that users will mostly need to navigate in sequence, only show the previous and next links. Stack them  vertically, like this:

{{ example({group: "components", item: "pagination", example: "labels", html: true, nunjucks: true, open: false, size: "s"}) }}

You can use the link labels to provide additional context.

{{ example({group: "components", item: "pagination", example: "labels-2", html: true, nunjucks: true, open: false, size: "s"}) }}

For pages where users might need to jump multiple pages forwards or backwards, add numbered page links, as well as the previous and next links, like this:

{{ example({group: "components", item: "pagination", example: "default", html: true, nunjucks: true, open: false, size: "s"}) }}

Show the page number in the title of the page so the user can see it in browser tabs and bookmarks. For example 'Search results (page 1 of 4)'.

Do not show pagination if there's only one page of content.

Redirect users to the first page if they enter a URL of a page that no longer exists.

### Previous and next links

Previous and next links are labelled 'Previous page' and 'Next page'. The word
'page' can be visually hidden to conserve horizontal space.

{{ example({group: "components", item: "pagination", example: "default", html: true, nunjucks: true, open: false, size: "s"}) }}

You can provide custom text for previous and next links if you need to.

{{ example({group: "components", item: "pagination", example: "custom-link-text", html: true, nunjucks: true, open: false, size: "s"}) }}

Do not show the previous page link on the first page — and do not show the next page link on the last page.

