### Showing large numbers of pages

Use ellipses (`…`) to skip over pages when needed.

{{ example({group: "components", item: "pagination", example: "ellipses", html: true, nunjucks: true, open: false, size: "s"}) }}

Adjust the page numbers shown to fit the horizontal space available.

On smaller screens only the first, last, current, previous and next pages will be shown.

Be sure to:
- include the first, last and current page
- include at least one page immediately before and after the current page
- replace gaps of 2 or more pages with ellipses (`…`)

For example:
- **[1]** 2 … 100
- 1 **[2]** 3 … 100
- 1 2 **[3]** 4 … 100
- 1 2 3 **[4]** 5 … 100
- 1 … 4 **[5]** 6 … 100
- 1 … 97 **[98]** 99 100
- 1 … 98 **[99]** 100
- 1 … 99 **[100]**

